01:08.524 --> 01:11.867
Uh, did you see that one guy
actually feeling the wood?

01:11.902 --> 01:14.036
I mean, seriously. Who feels wood?

01:14.071 --> 01:15.404
People who come to an open house.

01:16.238 --> 01:17.239
I guess. It's just...

01:17.273 --> 01:20.575
It's so weird having everyone
touch my things, you know?

01:20.609 --> 01:24.102
And be so judgmental of my home.

01:24.188 --> 01:27.023
Maybe so, but on the plus
side, it went really well.

01:27.148 --> 01:28.348
I'd be surprised if we didn't

01:28.382 --> 01:29.828
have at least two offers by tomorrow.

01:30.384 --> 01:31.452
[Knock on door]

01:31.928 --> 01:34.287
Oh, hey. Uh, I'm sorry. Did I

01:34.322 --> 01:36.852
- miss the open house?
- It ended about 30 minutes ago,

01:36.877 --> 01:39.016
but you can always make an
appointment to come see it.

01:40.572 --> 01:42.232
- Are you the owner?
- Yeah.

01:42.801 --> 01:44.302
Your house is great.

01:45.740 --> 01:47.741
Saw the pictures on the website.

01:48.173 --> 01:49.941
It's even better in person.

01:51.764 --> 01:54.094
I'm... I'm Zack.

01:54.126 --> 01:55.200
Savannah.

01:56.089 --> 01:57.653
Like I said, feel free to give me a call

01:57.678 --> 01:58.940
and we can set something up.

01:59.648 --> 02:00.691
Sure thing.

02:01.293 --> 02:03.194
Nice meeting you, Savannah.

02:09.365 --> 02:10.532
I'm telling you,

02:10.566 --> 02:12.971
multiple offers are a real possibility.

02:13.065 --> 02:15.366
You should let Harry know
this could be happening soon.

02:15.487 --> 02:17.522
Mm, that might be kind of difficult,

02:17.547 --> 02:20.216
considering that he is
still not speaking with me.

02:20.376 --> 02:22.577
Do you think maybe you
could fill him in for me?

02:22.611 --> 02:24.506
- Not a problem.
- Thank you, Vanessa.

02:25.448 --> 02:28.283
[Sighs]

02:31.583 --> 02:35.212
- sync and corrections by Albanda -
- www.Addic7ed.com -

02:38.048 --> 02:39.515
All right, Lucy, we're here.

02:39.549 --> 02:41.084
[Cellphone beeping]

02:41.747 --> 02:43.023
Lucy.

02:44.197 --> 02:45.922
- Lucy!
- What?! Why are you yelling at me?!

02:45.956 --> 02:47.023
Well, because apparently

02:47.057 --> 02:48.724
that's the only way to get your attention.

02:48.759 --> 02:50.726
We're here. Can I have
my phone back, please?

02:50.761 --> 02:52.610
Sorry. I'm in the middle of a game.

02:52.635 --> 02:53.681
[Scoffs]

02:53.878 --> 02:56.124
Ah, you seem to be on
my phone more than I am.

02:56.149 --> 02:59.349
<i>Well, if I had my own phone,
this would not be a problem.</i>

02:59.383 --> 03:01.351
Mm-hmm. You've mentioned that.

03:01.385 --> 03:02.552
Just so you know,

03:02.586 --> 03:04.654
I am the only one in my
class who does not have one.

03:04.688 --> 03:08.730
Okay, I understand this is a
transition for you, sweetie,

03:08.785 --> 03:10.260
and I know you want to fit in.

03:10.791 --> 03:13.092
But having expensive things
isn't the way to do it.

03:13.475 --> 03:14.731
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

03:14.765 --> 03:17.583
- [Sighs]
- [School bell rings]

03:17.855 --> 03:20.156
I am not trying to lecture you.

03:20.181 --> 03:21.978
I just don't want you to get all caught up

03:22.003 --> 03:24.146
thinking you have to
impress everyone, okay?

03:24.334 --> 03:26.670
- Okay.
- Bye.

03:27.974 --> 03:29.456
Felicia: April!

03:29.491 --> 03:30.924
Woman of the hour.

03:30.958 --> 03:33.649
Everyone is so excited for
your parent party tonight.

03:33.688 --> 03:35.462
Thanks, Felicia. I think it's gonna be fun.

03:35.497 --> 03:37.464
Listing it in the school party book

03:37.499 --> 03:39.633
as just "party" was brilliant.

03:39.668 --> 03:41.309
Now everybody's dying to know the theme.

03:42.208 --> 03:44.203
- The theme?
- You know, theme.

03:44.237 --> 03:46.706
The hook. What makes it crazy and special.

03:46.740 --> 03:49.475
Last year, someone actually
had the USC marching band.

03:50.201 --> 03:53.713
Oh, no marching bands for me.

03:53.747 --> 03:55.871
Shh! Don't tell me. I want to be surprised.

03:55.957 --> 03:58.737
Okay, I won't say a word. Hmm.

03:58.768 --> 04:01.203
You will definitely be surprised.

04:01.237 --> 04:03.165
[Chuckles] Victoria!

04:04.075 --> 04:05.088
See you later.

04:06.909 --> 04:08.869
I thought you said he was cute.

04:08.904 --> 04:11.279
<i>He was cute, but he kept talking about</i>

04:11.342 --> 04:13.310
his house that he has in Mexico,

04:13.437 --> 04:15.250
which he pronounced "me-hee-co."

04:15.638 --> 04:17.106
Dude is whiter than me.

04:17.543 --> 04:20.116
I got to go. I'm meeting Jacob for coffee.

04:20.173 --> 04:21.668
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa!

04:21.694 --> 04:23.540
Sister, sit your butt
back down in that chair.

04:25.427 --> 04:27.116
Are we talking about the same Jacob

04:27.140 --> 04:28.531
that reported you to the psych ward

04:28.556 --> 04:29.891
to get your license suspended?

04:29.949 --> 04:31.143
That's the one.

04:31.177 --> 04:32.820
Okay. Why are you having coffee with him?

04:33.222 --> 04:36.148
He said it was work related,
but he was kind of vague.

04:36.182 --> 04:38.348
Hey, do you think that maybe
he found out that you have

04:38.373 --> 04:40.875
a private practice and he's trying
to get your suspension extended?

04:40.900 --> 04:42.587
I hadn't thought of that.

04:42.621 --> 04:44.789
But thank you for putting that in my head.

04:44.823 --> 04:46.460
It's what... been a
year? I'm sure it's fine.

04:46.485 --> 04:48.213
Nobody holds on to anger that long.

04:48.697 --> 04:49.704
Joss!

04:50.748 --> 04:51.805
<i>Well, most people don't.</i>

04:51.830 --> 04:53.630
- Josslyn!
- Oh.

04:53.665 --> 04:54.865
- I'm gonna go.
- Yeah.

04:54.900 --> 04:57.101
All right. Mwah. Love you.

04:57.135 --> 04:58.317
Love you.

04:58.342 --> 04:59.503
[Groans]

05:00.205 --> 05:02.339
Hold your Australian horses.

05:02.364 --> 05:03.497
This person calls my house

05:03.522 --> 05:05.404
"an offense to people
with taste"... An offense.

05:05.429 --> 05:06.756
Okay. Harry, stop that. I told you

05:06.781 --> 05:07.811
not to look at the real-estate website.

05:07.845 --> 05:09.436
And everyone hated the
color of the guest room.

05:09.461 --> 05:10.556
-  Everyone.
- [Chuckles]

05:10.581 --> 05:13.049
You do understand that
nobody reads those comments.

05:13.084 --> 05:14.657
- W-who are you texting?
- My painter.

05:14.691 --> 05:17.095
I told Savi over and
over we need to upgrade

05:17.120 --> 05:19.218
that guest room before
it goes on the market.

05:19.243 --> 05:20.497
Actually, correction.

05:20.522 --> 05:22.461
<i>You told me over and over
again, and I told Savi.</i>

05:22.504 --> 05:24.069
Right, so tell her the
painter is coming today

05:24.094 --> 05:25.127
- between...
- No!

05:25.161 --> 05:26.795
No. That's not happening.

05:26.830 --> 05:28.985
I'm not... I'm not gonna be
the go-between anymore, Harry.

05:29.045 --> 05:30.446
Okay. Joss, look. I know...

05:30.471 --> 05:32.864
- I know that this is awkward for you.
- Just call her!

05:32.889 --> 05:34.419
It will take all of five minutes.

05:34.473 --> 05:36.551
- I-I don't want to call her.
- Fine.

05:36.589 --> 05:38.075
If you can't talk to her, then text her.

05:38.100 --> 05:40.721
That's why texting was invented...
T o avoid any chance of intimacy.

05:40.746 --> 05:42.617
Joss, just one last thing,
okay? And then that's...

05:42.642 --> 05:43.609
that's it. And then you can be done.

05:43.674 --> 05:44.904
Harry, do you understand?

05:44.929 --> 05:46.385
This is exactly why we
can't work together...

05:46.419 --> 05:47.806
This right here. Sorry.

05:47.831 --> 05:49.283
Joss! Joss.

05:52.959 --> 05:54.819
I can't. I can't.

05:55.021 --> 05:57.231
If I could... if I could call her,

05:57.297 --> 05:58.696
if I could see her, I...

05:59.632 --> 06:01.069
But I just... I cannot, okay?

06:01.112 --> 06:02.990
So, yeah, I'm asking for your help.

06:03.385 --> 06:06.083
But not as my partner, as my friend.

06:07.939 --> 06:09.173
Please?

06:09.208 --> 06:10.806
[Sighs]

06:13.112 --> 06:15.746
I say things I don't mean all the time.

06:15.780 --> 06:17.215
Why do you think I'm a lawyer?

06:17.476 --> 06:20.351
<i>That's what depositions are for. Adios.</i>

06:20.385 --> 06:21.519
[Cellphone beeps]

06:21.553 --> 06:23.750
Don't get mad at me for
what I'm about to say,

06:23.782 --> 06:25.521
but I have to say it.

06:25.608 --> 06:27.176
You look amazing.

06:27.493 --> 06:31.261
<i>You really know how to bounce
back from a crash, mamacita.</i>

06:31.295 --> 06:34.479
[Chuckles] Thank you. I try.

06:34.899 --> 06:38.381
So, are you married? Single?

06:38.514 --> 06:39.536
Lesbian?

06:39.570 --> 06:41.710
I am married.

06:41.859 --> 06:44.439
I'm actually going through a divorce.

06:46.038 --> 06:48.140
So I guess that means I'm single.

06:48.613 --> 06:51.474
<i>Fantastico. Then we
should go out, you and I.</i>

06:51.915 --> 06:54.146
- As singles, not lesbians.
- You know what?

06:54.171 --> 06:56.686
I'm really not into the
dating scene right now

06:56.711 --> 06:58.888
as a straight person or a gay person.

06:58.922 --> 07:01.025
No, no, no, no, no. Just for fun.

07:01.050 --> 07:03.561
Because... don't tell anyone, but

07:04.141 --> 07:07.897
things between Dom and
I are getting hotter.

07:08.507 --> 07:10.644
- Really?
- Yeah.

07:11.035 --> 07:13.097
We were here, just us the other morning,

07:13.122 --> 07:17.339
and he accidentally rubbed
my elbow three times.

07:18.152 --> 07:19.408
It was like electricity,

07:19.442 --> 07:22.227
like lightning bolts up and down my spine.

07:22.252 --> 07:24.931
Ooh. It's a good thing you
didn't get electrocuted.

07:25.454 --> 07:26.920
[Knocks on door]

07:26.945 --> 07:27.945
Hey, lady.

07:29.850 --> 07:31.006
<i>[Cellphone rings] Ã¿QuÃ© pasÃ³?</i>

07:32.237 --> 07:33.255
<i>Well, she's not ugly.</i>

07:33.290 --> 07:35.511
Yeah, welcome to my hell.

07:35.536 --> 07:37.101
So, Harry wanted me to tell you that he

07:37.126 --> 07:38.722
hired a painter to
repaint the guest bedroom.

07:38.747 --> 07:40.662
We don't need to be putting
any more money into the house,

07:40.697 --> 07:41.763
people are loving it.

07:41.798 --> 07:43.580
We're about to get multiple offers on it...

07:43.605 --> 07:44.771
- Multiple!
- Easy.

07:44.796 --> 07:46.662
Don't inappropriately
scream at the messenger.

07:46.687 --> 07:48.013
I'm sorry. I just... I don't want

07:48.038 --> 07:50.107
there to be a messenger anymore, okay?

07:50.132 --> 07:51.600
I want to talk to Harry

07:51.625 --> 07:54.594
like two normal people who
spent 15 years together.

07:54.681 --> 07:56.354
Yeah, but, Savi, the guy's really hurting.

07:56.379 --> 07:59.203
Just... just... he'll eventually
get there. Give him some time.

07:59.269 --> 08:01.140
You know what? I'm calling him right now.

08:01.179 --> 08:03.084
Or just completely ignore me.

08:03.109 --> 08:05.038
<i>- [Ringing]
- Harry: Hey. It's Harry. Leave a message</i>

08:05.063 --> 08:07.045
<i>- I'll call you back. [Beep]
- [Scoffs]</i>

08:07.070 --> 08:09.924
Straight to voice-mail.
No big surprise there.

08:10.326 --> 08:12.260
Please tell him no painters, okay?

08:12.285 --> 08:13.519
It's crazy.

08:13.544 --> 08:15.760
Well, that's kind of a problem
because I think the guy's

08:15.785 --> 08:17.846
already on his way to
your house with paint.

08:19.510 --> 08:20.653
Damn it.

08:22.625 --> 08:24.094
Craziness.

08:24.298 --> 08:26.399
[Chuckles] Great chat.

08:26.574 --> 08:28.542
[Telephone ringing]

08:28.576 --> 08:30.878
Hey. I need a favor.

08:30.912 --> 08:32.212
Well, hello to you, too.

08:32.246 --> 08:33.513
I'm sorry.

08:33.548 --> 08:35.850
I-I just... I-I have to
go home for a little bit.

08:35.884 --> 08:38.018
- Is everything okay?
- Yeah, everything is fine.

08:38.053 --> 08:39.686
But, uh, if I don't get home soon,

08:39.721 --> 08:42.011
I'm gonna wind up wasting
$1,000 that I don't have

08:42.046 --> 08:44.080
to paint a room that
doesn't need to be painted.

08:44.470 --> 08:46.352
Well, couldn't you just
call off the painter?

08:46.377 --> 08:47.861
[Sighing] Oh, I would love to do that,

08:47.895 --> 08:50.701
but I don't have his number
because he's Harry's guy.

08:50.726 --> 08:53.360
It's Harry's guy. Oh.

08:53.508 --> 08:54.950
Look. Um...

08:55.755 --> 08:58.151
I don't know what to say here.
I mean, w-we have the meeting

08:58.199 --> 09:00.238
- with the Tanner brothers and...
- I know. I know. And

09:00.263 --> 09:02.367
I will definitely be back before then.

09:02.541 --> 09:04.768
I don't... [Groans]

09:05.133 --> 09:07.935
All right. You know what?
Don't... don't worry about it.

09:08.047 --> 09:09.514
I will ask Mitchell.

09:09.548 --> 09:11.448
- Yeah, but Mitchell will say no.
- I know. I know.

09:11.473 --> 09:13.273
And that's... it's okay.

09:13.410 --> 09:14.756
[Sighs] You know, go.

09:15.655 --> 09:18.599
Go, all right? Do what you got to do.

09:18.625 --> 09:20.096
I love you. I promise

09:20.121 --> 09:22.218
I won't let this become a thing.

09:32.374 --> 09:33.640
Paintball and Tequila.

09:33.674 --> 09:37.386
Cigar bar and scotch tasting.
Rollerskating and wine.

09:37.411 --> 09:39.898
Mm. Sensing an alcoholic theme.

09:40.380 --> 09:42.015
Oh, look. Here's yours.

09:42.769 --> 09:43.970
"Party."

09:44.217 --> 09:45.683
Very descriptive, April.

09:46.812 --> 09:48.686
You want to talk about
why Daniel isn't calling

09:48.721 --> 09:51.356
or you want to explain to
me what a parent party is?

09:51.391 --> 09:52.857
[Sighs] I'm open to either.

09:52.892 --> 09:55.174
They're like these mini fundraisers.

09:55.199 --> 09:57.529
The school asks parents to
throw parties for other parents

09:57.563 --> 09:58.946
and charge them to come

09:58.971 --> 10:01.389
so that they can give the
money back to the school.

10:01.414 --> 10:03.294
Why doesn't the school
just ask for more money?

10:03.319 --> 10:05.569
Because we're supposed to be having fun.

10:05.603 --> 10:06.737
See how much fun I'm having?

10:06.771 --> 10:09.206
So what is your party?

10:11.873 --> 10:13.110
Pizza and beer.

10:15.277 --> 10:16.647
I'm canceling.

10:16.681 --> 10:18.983
Better to have no party
than a terrible party.

10:19.017 --> 10:20.051
Cancel?!

10:20.085 --> 10:22.467
Two words, sweetie... "social suicide."

10:22.492 --> 10:24.997
<i>So what? It's not like
these are my real friends.</i>

10:25.022 --> 10:27.523
I'm not talking about you.
I'm talking about Lucy.

10:27.558 --> 10:28.691
You screw this up,

10:28.725 --> 10:30.817
she's Ralph Macchio
before he met Mr. Miyagi.

10:30.872 --> 10:32.059
Wax on.

10:32.106 --> 10:33.430
No, what you need to do is regroup

10:33.464 --> 10:35.598
and come up with something spectacular.

10:35.632 --> 10:37.267
In four hours?

10:37.301 --> 10:38.668
Even if Joss helped me, there is no...

10:38.702 --> 10:41.108
Who said anything about Joss?

10:42.244 --> 10:43.401
What...

10:44.306 --> 10:46.748
Oh. Hey, sweetie. Hey, Peyton.

10:46.773 --> 10:48.357
I didn't know you girls were coming over.

10:48.382 --> 10:51.653
I texted you from Peyton's
phone like an hour ago.

10:51.791 --> 10:54.259
What? I never... never got that.

10:54.284 --> 10:56.749
We just need a couple frappys,
and we'll be on our way.

10:56.774 --> 10:59.941
- Are you girls going to the mall?
- [Chuckles] The mall.

11:00.538 --> 11:02.710
Oh, I'm sorry. I thought that
was supposed to be a joke.

11:02.735 --> 11:04.168
Oh, we're going over to my house.

11:04.193 --> 11:05.894
My mom just put in a steam room.

11:05.989 --> 11:08.393
Oh. Well, that sounds nice, too.

11:08.957 --> 11:10.997
You know, Peyton, I would
love to meet your parents.

11:11.031 --> 11:14.033
- Are they coming to my party tonight?
- The one called "party"?

11:15.235 --> 11:16.503
Doubtful.

11:17.739 --> 11:19.121
[Cellphone clicking]

11:19.146 --> 11:22.074
They can do cocktails
Thursday between 5:30 and 6:30,

11:22.403 --> 11:23.643
if that works for you.

11:23.850 --> 11:26.661
That works for me. Thank you, Peyton.

11:26.686 --> 11:27.753
No prob.

11:27.778 --> 11:29.949
- So how about those frappys?
- Oh.

11:31.201 --> 11:32.869
No frappys.

11:35.189 --> 11:36.948
Just juice boxes.

11:42.657 --> 11:44.141
I had a lot of concerns

11:44.166 --> 11:46.446
with his consistency with the medication.

11:46.471 --> 11:48.438
I wasn't sure how many
doses he was skipping.

11:48.831 --> 11:50.833
Yeah. Well, I guess he, uh...

11:51.363 --> 11:53.817
Doesn't come across as
the most reliable patient.

11:53.842 --> 11:55.409
I'll keep that in mind.

11:56.823 --> 11:58.308
- [Sighs]
- So, you look...

11:58.333 --> 12:00.634
I've been meaning to thank
you. Oh. I'm so sorry.

12:00.659 --> 12:02.493
- No, uh, you... go ahead.
- [Sighs]

12:02.518 --> 12:03.854
I know I didn't call you back,

12:03.879 --> 12:06.380
but, um, I appreciated your message.

12:07.180 --> 12:08.579
Not many people know what to say

12:08.604 --> 12:09.905
to a person who's been shot at.

12:09.930 --> 12:12.560
But you, you were good.

12:13.975 --> 12:16.382
I'm just glad you're okay.

12:16.760 --> 12:18.578
You still working at the hospital?

12:20.220 --> 12:24.231
Actually, I just started on
my private practice again.

12:24.256 --> 12:26.623
Oh, that's... that's great to hear.

12:27.533 --> 12:28.848
I'm so relieved.

12:28.873 --> 12:32.008
Honestly, I was nervous about
reaching out to you today.

12:32.725 --> 12:35.138
I was such an ass,

12:35.708 --> 12:37.273
reporting you to the board like that.

12:37.683 --> 12:39.417
You did the right thing, Jacob.

12:39.515 --> 12:40.515
Maybe.

12:41.546 --> 12:43.299
But I did it for the wrong reasons.

12:43.397 --> 12:46.094
I was hurt that you didn't
reciprocate my feelings.

12:46.740 --> 12:47.928
Your feelings?

12:50.148 --> 12:52.008
<i>Romantic feelings?</i>

12:52.404 --> 12:55.646
You're kidding, right? What?
Y-you seriously didn't know?

12:56.228 --> 12:58.390
Um... No.

12:59.208 --> 13:01.009
How would I have known?

13:01.058 --> 13:02.115
[Chuckling] I...

13:02.597 --> 13:05.165
I guess I need to work
on my flirting techniques.

13:05.317 --> 13:08.158
Huh. I always thought I was so smooth.

13:08.555 --> 13:11.190
Well, I-I got to get back to the office.

13:11.215 --> 13:13.773
But, um, we should... we
should do this again some time.

13:13.798 --> 13:14.914
I'll... I'll call you.

13:15.532 --> 13:16.803
That sounds great.

13:17.549 --> 13:20.017
[Both chuckle]

13:25.571 --> 13:26.681
[Sighs]

13:27.267 --> 13:29.234
Oh, my God!

13:29.292 --> 13:31.494
I have had it with the
better business bureau!

13:31.519 --> 13:33.186
Seriously, what? Better than who?

13:33.211 --> 13:34.883
From where I sit, it's all spin.

13:35.645 --> 13:37.613
Yep. Great.

13:38.069 --> 13:39.814
Okay. Yeah. Thank you.

13:40.990 --> 13:43.848
This is a phone. When
someone's holding it to his ear,

13:43.873 --> 13:46.002
it usually means he's
talking to someone else.

13:46.027 --> 13:48.385
Okay. Well, what's got
all up in your bloomers?

13:48.410 --> 13:50.301
My bloomers are fine. That was Vanessa.

13:50.326 --> 13:51.935
We just got a cash offer for the house.

13:51.960 --> 13:53.261
- [Gasps] No.
- Boom.

13:53.286 --> 13:54.419
- Already?
- Yep.

13:54.444 --> 13:56.915
- That's amazing! Mazel tov, man.
- Thank you.

14:00.725 --> 14:03.233
Oh, uh, please tell me that
this isn't the whole offer.

14:03.258 --> 14:05.040
It's a bit under the asking, I know.

14:05.065 --> 14:08.036
But it's solid and it's cash, and
cash makes things go much more quickly.

14:08.036 --> 14:11.132
<i>A bit under? Harry, that's like
saying the Titanic was a bit under.</i>

14:11.157 --> 14:13.959
This is... no. Savi... Savi's
never gonna accept this.

14:14.000 --> 14:16.171
She will when you use
your real-estate expertise

14:16.196 --> 14:18.097
to convince her it's an amazing deal.

14:19.525 --> 14:20.826
Okay.

14:20.851 --> 14:22.785
First of all, nice try on the flattery.

14:22.810 --> 14:24.795
<i>Second of all, that is not an amazing deal.</i>

14:24.820 --> 14:26.378
And third of all, you need to call her.

14:27.323 --> 14:29.683
Harry, I-I know you're angry
and you have every right to be,

14:29.708 --> 14:32.227
but you can't just ignore her
and never speak to her again.

14:32.252 --> 14:33.485
It's not realistic.

14:33.510 --> 14:36.301
I really do not want to have
this conversation right now.

14:36.520 --> 14:39.322
Fine. But I-I'm not having
that conversation with Savi.

14:39.347 --> 14:42.241
If you want to accept that offer,
you're gonna have to call her yourself.

14:47.718 --> 14:49.033
[Elevator bell dings]

14:51.173 --> 14:52.788
- Take care.
- Please.

14:56.091 --> 14:57.237
[Clears throat]

14:59.983 --> 15:01.371
I am so sorry.

15:02.285 --> 15:04.928
The painter wouldn't leave
until he spoke to Harry directly,

15:04.953 --> 15:07.255
who picked up the call
right away, of course.

15:07.557 --> 15:09.853
And then his truck wouldn't
start, so I had to call AAA.

15:09.878 --> 15:12.012
You know, Savi, it's, uh... it's fine.

15:12.090 --> 15:14.557
No, no. It's not fine. You're angry.

15:14.582 --> 15:16.882
No, I'm... I'm not angry. Do I seem angry?

15:16.951 --> 15:19.418
Uh... Yeah. A little.

15:19.500 --> 15:21.568
Well, I'm not. I'm just busy.

15:21.702 --> 15:24.561
And Toni covered for you in the
meeting, so it's no big deal.

15:24.586 --> 15:26.453
Yeah, I-I noticed that she was here.

15:26.515 --> 15:27.908
<i>[Chuckles] Okay, I-I know</i>

15:27.933 --> 15:29.390
you're not gonna go there right now

15:29.415 --> 15:31.616
<i>because if you went there,
then I might get angry.</i>

15:31.641 --> 15:33.171
Toni covered your ass in that meeting,

15:33.196 --> 15:35.197
so whatever issues you
have with her, please...

15:35.222 --> 15:37.524
No, no, no, I don't have
any issues with Toni,

15:37.679 --> 15:39.764
except for the fact
that she keeps telling me

15:39.789 --> 15:42.991
how electric it is every
time you touch her elbow.

15:43.016 --> 15:44.250
Okay, I'm... I'm...

15:44.275 --> 15:46.136
I'm gonna pretend like
I didn't even hear that.

15:46.236 --> 15:49.410
[Sighs] Look. [Clears throat]

15:49.460 --> 15:52.054
The fact is, I never
should have let you go.

15:52.861 --> 15:54.558
Here, I am your boss.

15:54.583 --> 15:56.006
And that's all there is to it.

15:56.078 --> 15:58.065
I gave you the option to
play the boyfriend card,

15:58.090 --> 16:00.825
and you took it and abused it.

16:00.850 --> 16:02.226
No, Dom. That's not what I did.

16:02.251 --> 16:05.053
It is. It is. But a little piece of advice.

16:05.111 --> 16:06.640
If you play that card in the future,

16:06.671 --> 16:09.540
don't use problems with your
ex-husband to convince me.

16:10.652 --> 16:11.656
[Sighs]

16:22.557 --> 16:25.559
